public abstract class AbstractModelProvider<M extends Model,B extends DataSource>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ModelProvider<M,B>

Abstract class, which simplifies implementation of ModelProvider. It uses class hierarchy to compute priority of providers.

public abstract M createModelFor(B app)
This is factory method for creating new instance of Model for DataSource. Implementation of this method should return null if this model provider cannot construct model for passed dataSource.

priority

public int priority()
Description copied from interface: ModelProvider
Priority is used by ModelFactory to sort registered ModelProvider. Model provider with the highest priority will be invoked first and so no, until non-null value is returned from ModelProvider.createModelFor(DataSource )

Specified by:
priority in interface ModelProvider<M extends Model,B extends DataSource>
